==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Coöperation
<hw>Co*⟦oum⟧p`er*a"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>cooperatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>coop⟦eacute⟧ration</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of cooperating, or of operating together to one
end; joint operation; concurrent effort or labor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Not holpen by the <qex>cooperation</qex> of angels.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Polit. Econ.)</fld> <def>The association of a
number of persons for their benefit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cooperative</ent>⟦br⟧
